# Best Practices

When maintaining or extending this website, follow these guidelines:

## HTML Structure ([index.html](mdc:index.html))
- Use semantic HTML5 elements
- Maintain mobile-first responsive design
- Keep accessibility in mind with proper ARIA attributes
- Preserve the existing class naming conventions
- Use Font Awesome for icons when possible

## CSS Guidelines ([styles.css](mdc:styles.css))
- Follow the existing modular CSS structure
- Maintain the established responsive breakpoints
- Use relative units (em, %, vh) over fixed units
- Keep the cascading order of styles:
  1. Reset/Base styles
  2. Layout styles
  3. Component styles
  4. Responsive adjustments

## Asset Management
- Store images in the `images/` directory
- Keep icons in the `icons/` directory
- Optimize images before adding to the project
- Use SVG for icons when possible

## Performance Considerations
- Minimize external dependencies
- Use system fonts or Google Fonts
- Maintain efficient CSS selectors
- Keep image sizes optimized for web

## Version Control
- Keep meaningful commit messages
- Document any major layout or style changes
- Test responsive behavior before committing
- Maintain backwards compatibility
